---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import commands from "../generated/cli-commands.json";
---
<Base title="Docs">
  <h1>brna documentation</h1>
  <p class="muted">CLI reference and agent integration guidance for React Native dev sessions.</p>

  <p>
    brna is an <strong>agent-time inspect/act primitive</strong> for React
    Native development. It is not an end-to-end test runner and is not a
    replacement for Maestro, Detox, or Appium. Use brna when you want a
    coding agent to read the current screen of a running dev app and drive
    it with stable selectors; reach for an E2E runner when you need recorded
    test suites or production app coverage.
  </p>

  <input class="search" type="search" placeholder="Search commands and guides" data-search />

  <section class="grid" data-results>
    {commands.map((command) => (
      <article class="card" data-index={`${command.name} ${command.description} ${command.examples.join(" ")}`}>
        <h3>{command.name}</h3>
        <p>{command.description}</p>
        <a href="/cli">CLI reference</a>
      </article>
    ))}
    <article class="card" data-index="mcp agents integration tools snapshot action selector">
      <h3>Agent integration</h3>
      <p>Connect MCP clients to a running brna runtime and dispatch actions from selectors.</p>
      <a href="/agents">Agent guide</a>
    </article>
    <article class="card" data-index="cookbook trace mcp tdd test driven development examples yaml replay">
      <h3>MCP Trace Examples & Cookbooks</h3>
      <p>Replayable <code>.yaml</code> traces showing agent-driven TDD workflows against a running app.</p>
      <a href="/cookbooks">Cookbooks</a>
    </article>
    <article class="card" data-index="local usage privacy journal telemetry summary export retention disable clear">
      <h3>Local usage and privacy</h3>
      <p>Inspect agent usage patterns locally, control collection, and create aggregate-only reports.</p>
      <a href="/usage">Usage journal guide</a>
    </article>
  </section>

  <script>
    const input = document.querySelector("[data-search]");
    const cards = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll("[data-index]"));
    input?.addEventListener("input", () => {
      const q = input.value.toLowerCase();
      for (const card of cards) {
        const hit = card.getAttribute("data-index")?.toLowerCase().includes(q);
        card.toggleAttribute("hidden", q.length > 0 && !hit);
      }
    });
  </script>
</Base>
